extremeStackDetection.name: extremeStackDetection
extremeStackDetection.description: This field provides the information as to whether the stacking is enabled (True) or disabled (False) for the system. The stacking feature is supported from extremeware version 7.4 and above

extremeStackMemberTable.name: extremeStackMemberTable
extremeStackMemberTable.description: A table containing information about each stack member that are a part of this stacking. If extremeStackDetection is not enabled, we wouldnt not have any rows for this table.

extremeStackMemberEntry.name: extremeStackMemberEntry
extremeStackMemberEntry.description: Entry in the table for a StackMember Entity

extremeStackMemberSlotId.name: extremeStackMemberSlotId
extremeStackMemberSlotId.description: The slot id of the stack member in the stack

extremeStackMemberType.name: extremeStackMemberType
extremeStackMemberType.description: The type of device of the stack member. This field reflects the individual sysOid of the member

extremeStackMemberOperStatus.name: extremeStackMemberOperStatus
extremeStackMemberOperStatus.description: The operational status of the stack member. When the stack comes up, if there is a vector mismatch namely license mismatch or platform mismatch between the master and the member, the member remains in the mismatch state. Further communication with the member is not possible

extremeStackMemberRole.name: extremeStackMemberRole
extremeStackMemberRole.description: The role of the stack member as to whether it is acting as a master or a slave

extremeStackMemberEntPhysicalIndex.name: extremeStackMemberEntPhysicalIndex
extremeStackMemberEntPhysicalIndex.description: The entPhysicalIndex of the corresponding device as defined in the ENTITY-MIB

extremeStackMemberMACAddress.name: extremeStackMemberMACAddress
extremeStackMemberMACAddress.description: The Mac address of the stack member

extremeStackMemberCurImageVersion.name: extremeStackMemberCurImageVersion
extremeStackMemberCurImageVersion.description: The current image version of the stack member

extremeStackMemberPriImageVersion.name: extremeStackMemberPriImageVersion
extremeStackMemberPriImageVersion.description: The primary image version of the stack member

extremeStackMemberSecImageVersion.name: extremeStackMemberSecImageVersion
extremeStackMemberSecImageVersion.description: The secondary image version of the stack member

extremeStackMemberBootRomVersion.name: extremeStackMemberBootRomVersion
extremeStackMemberBootRomVersion.description: The boot rom version of the stack member

extremeStackMemberCurConfig.name: extremeStackMemberCurConfig
extremeStackMemberCurConfig.description: The current configuration of the stack member

extremeStackMemberConfigSelected.name: extremeStackMemberConfigSelected
extremeStackMemberConfigSelected.description: The config selected to be used on reboot for the stack member

extremeStackMemberImageSelected.name: extremeStackMemberImageSelected
extremeStackMemberImageSelected.description: The image selected to be used on reboot for the stack member

extremeStackMemberStackPriority.name: extremeStackMemberStackPriority
extremeStackMemberStackPriority.description: The stack priority of the stack member. The stack priority is used for the master election algorithm. The member with the highest priority comes up as the master. If there are more than one switch with highest priority, the member with the least MAC among them comes up as the master

extremeStackMemberMgmtIpAddress.name: extremeStackMemberMgmtIpAddress
extremeStackMemberMgmtIpAddress.description: The fallback mgmt ip address which was configured through CLI for this stack member. This ipaddress can be used to communicate with this member, if it comes up as the master. The ipaddress is associated with the vlan configured

extremeStackMemberSysLocation.name: extremeStackMemberSysLocation
extremeStackMemberSysLocation.description: The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor'). If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

extremeStackMemberAutoConfig.name: extremeStackMemberAutoConfig
extremeStackMemberAutoConfig.description: This field provides the information whether the config of the stack member is autogenerated(true) or not(false)

extremeStackMemberStackStatus.name: extremeStackMemberStackStatus
extremeStackMemberStackStatus.description: This status is used for disabling the stacking feature for the stack member. If stacking is enabled for the stack member we get the information as enable, if we mark it as disable, the stack member is removed from the stack and the corresponding row disappears

extremeStackingPortTable.name: extremeStackingPortTable
extremeStackingPortTable.description: A table containing information about each stacking port in the stack. If extremeStackDetection is not enabled, we would not have any rows for this table

extremeStackingPortEntry.name: extremeStackingPortEntry
extremeStackingPortEntry.description: Entry in the table for each stacking port in the stack

extremeStackingPortIfIndex.name: extremeStackingPortIfIndex
extremeStackingPortIfIndex.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

extremeStackingPortRemoteMac.name: extremeStackingPortRemoteMac
extremeStackingPortRemoteMac.description: The Mac address of the remote system, this stacking port is connected to. The value of the mac address will be 00:00:00:00:00:00 if the stacking link is not active.

extremeStackingPortLinkSpeed.name: extremeStackingPortLinkSpeed
extremeStackingPortLinkSpeed.description: The Speed of the stacking port link in bps. The speed will be zero if the link is not up

extremeStackingPortLinkStatus.name: extremeStackingPortLinkStatus
extremeStackingPortLinkStatus.description: The Link status of the stacking port link

extremeStackMemberOverheat.name: extremeStackMemberOverheat
extremeStackMemberOverheat.description: The extremeStackMemberOverheat notification is generated when the temperature of the stack member reaches the threshold temperature

extremeStackMemberStatusChanged.name: extremeStackMemberStatusChanged
extremeStackMemberStatusChanged.description: The extremeStackMemberStatusChanged notification is generated when the operational status of the stack member changes

extremeStackingPortStatusChanged.name: extremeStackingPortStatusChanged
extremeStackingPortStatusChanged.description: The extremeStackingPortStatusChanged notification is generated when the operational status of the stacking port changes
